# Qwik web-public surface for `<project-name>` (2.0.0 candidate)

This directory is the **2.0.0 web-public delta** for the `full-stack-monorepo`
flagship. It introduces a **Qwik City** public-facing web surface, authored as an
**additive** sibling alongside the frozen flat 1.0.0 template tree and the existing
`web-backoffice` Flutter-Web surface. It removes nothing. Standard:
`.forge/standards/web-frontend.yaml`.

> **Status**: `candidate` — **`scaffoldable: false` until B.8.14**. The
> `full-stack-monorepo / 2.0.0` schema is a `candidate`; this subtree is an additive
> on-disk asset spliced into the 2.0.0 stack at B.8.10/B.8.14. `forge init` still
> emits the flat 1.0.0 tree (no web-public surface) by default.

## Delivery model

A minimal, chart-less Qwik City skeleton (10 template files) demonstrating SSR,
routing, a Connect-ES client (one unary call), and the Node toolchain pin. It is
the policy-sourced realisation of `web-frontend.yaml` v1.0.0 (`default: qwik-city`,
ratifying ADR-005 — `docs/ARCHITECTURE-TARGET.md:365-374`). B.8.9 change context:
KEEP Flutter mobile+desktop+backoffice, REPLACE the Flutter Web *public* surface →
Qwik City (SEO / resumability / LCP / TTI).

The skeleton is deliberately trimmed (no eslint/prettier config, no PWA machinery,
no `public/` assets, no `global.css`) — those are adopter concerns or later bricks
(see Scope out). The official Qwik starter's eslint/prettier are omitted on purpose;
the adopter adds their lint tooling.

