## Governance — Janus arbitration (until Iris-Web / K.4)

Janus arbitrates the `web-public` and `web-backoffice` surfaces for cross-layer
changes that span them, until the **Iris-Web** agent ships (K.4, T7 — the
web-frontend specialist). Until then, `web-frontend.yaml` machine enforcement
(`ci_blocking`, `linter_rule`) stays **OFF** — it is documentation-only at birth.
See `plan:2321` and `docs/ARCHITECTURE-TARGET.md:743` for the surface-split and
agent-handoff references.

## Envoy Connect/HTTP path

The Qwik client makes Connect-protocol HTTP calls; **Envoy Gateway (B.8.4)** is the
ingress (`AT C4: Rel(qwik, envoy)`). See `2.0.0/infra/k8s/envoy-gateway/` for the
Envoy template. The flow is: Qwik SSR/CSR → `createConnectTransport({ baseUrl })` →
Envoy Gateway → Rust Connect-RPC backend (B.8.6). JWT validation at the gateway and
the OIDC/PKCE client are later bricks (see Scope out).

## web-backoffice posture (unchanged)

The `web-backoffice` **Flutter Web** surface is **unchanged** by this brick. The
1.0.0 Flutter app already covers it; the 2.0.0 schema simply re-homes it under
`frontend/web-backoffice/` (ADR-B8-3-004). Any backoffice migration is B.8.10 /
B.8.14 territory. Article VI (Flutter mandate) is preserved — Qwik is an *additive
public-web* surface, not a Flutter replacement for mobile/desktop/backoffice.

## Node toolchain setup

This subtree ships `.nvmrc` (value: `24`, active LTS at 2026-06-03, re-verified at
implement). Use `nvm use` / `fnm use` or `actions/setup-node` with
`node-version-file: .nvmrc` in CI (mirrors the Flutter `flutter-version-file`
pattern). Node 24 satisfies Qwik 1.20.0 `engines.node` (`>=18.11`). Re-verify the
active LTS at each `pin_review_cadence` boundary (`node: P12M`; `web-frontend.yaml`).
The package manager is **npm** (matches the official Qwik starter posture; no
`.npmrc` shipped here — adopter concern).

## PITFALL — Vite 8 is excluded

`vite` 8.x is the npm `latest` but is **EXCLUDED** by `@builder.io/qwik`
peerDependencies `>=5 <8`. Pin to `=7.3.5` **exactly** (the max stable 7.x).
Installing the default vite 8 yields an incompatible peer / broken build. See the
`web-frontend.yaml` `versions` block for the current pin and ADR-B89-001 for the
rationale.

## Connect-ES usage

`src/lib/connect-client.ts` wires a Connect-ES v2 **browser** client:
`createConnectTransport` from `@connectrpc/connect-web` + `createClient` from
`@connectrpc/connect`. The generated `GreeterService` descriptor is buf-generated by
the **es plugin** (`buf.build/bufbuild/es:v2.2.0`, `target=ts`) into
`src/lib/generated/connect/` — the ADR-B89-004 re-pointed `buf.gen` output path. Run
`task proto` (or `cd shared/protos && buf generate`) to materialise it.

> **Note**: the stale `protoc-gen-connect-es` naming is **retired by Connect v2**.
> The correct codegen tool is `buf.build/bufbuild/es:v2.2.0` (a single `*_pb` file
> carries the service descriptor — Connect v2 removed the separate `*_connect` file).

## Zod deferral

Connect-ES client + **Zod** schemas are **deferred per ADR-B89-003** — protobuf-es
v2 generates TypeScript types directly, which suffice for this skeleton. Revisit Zod
at B.9.2 (PWA) or the next brick requiring client-side validation (forms, env-var
validation). `AT:612` reference recorded.

## Scope out (this brick)

- **PWA machinery** (Service Worker, Web Push/VAPID, offline shell) → **B.9.2**
- **OIDC/PKCE Qwik client** (token storage, refresh) → **B.9.3**
- **OTel wiring from Qwik** (`Rel(qwik, otel)` OTLP export) → **B.8.12 / B.7**
- **Streaming patterns** (SSE / WebTransport / cancel-on-unmount) → **B.7.10**
- **Hosting tier rows** (Cloudflare Pages / Vercel / OVH) → **B.9.7**
- **Iris-Web agent** (web-frontend specialist) → **K.4 (T7)**
- **Adopter CI workflow for the web surface** (`forge-web.yml`) → **B.8.10** (lean defer)

## Template variables

This skeleton uses angle-bracket template variables (FR-B89-004):

- `<project-name>` — package name, page title/heading
- `<namespace>` — deployment namespace (adopter-supplied)
- `<api-url>` — backend Connect/HTTP base URL (`src/lib/connect-client.ts`)

> **NEVER PUT SECRETS HERE.** The backend URL and any environment values are
> supplied at deploy time (e.g. `PUBLIC_API_URL` via the Vite env), never committed.
